  "prompt": "What are some good sources for free instrumental music to use in video tutorials?",
  "response": "There are several great sources for free instrumental music that you can use in video tutorials. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **YouTube Audio Library**: This is a fantastic resource where you can find a variety of free music and sound effects. You can filter the tracks by genre and mood, and usage is typically allowed for any YouTube videos.\n\n2. **Free Music Archive (FMA)**: A large archive of free music across various genres. You will find many instrumental tracks here, and you can filter by license type to ensure you can use them legally.\n\n3. **Incompetech**: Created by composer Kevin MacLeod, Incompetech offers a wide range of royalty-free music across multiple genres. Just be sure to credit the composer as required.\n\n4. **Bensound**: This site offers a variety of royalty-free music tracks that can be used in videos under a Creative Commons license. You can find instrumental options suited for different themes.\n\n5. **Musopen**: A nonprofit organization that provides free access to music recordings, sheet music, and educational materials. You can find classical and instrumental pieces available for use.\n\n6. **Jamendo**: This site hosts a large collection of music available under Creative Commons licenses, allowing you to search for instrumental tracks specifically.\n\n7. **SoundCloud**: While not all music on SoundCloud is free to use, there are many artists who offer their tracks under Creative Commons licenses. Just be sure to check the licensing before using it in your projects.\n\n8. **ccMixter**: A community music site featuring remixes and samples licensed under Creative Commons. You can find many instrumental tracks, often suitable for various video projects.\n\n9. **Audio Library (on YouTube)**: A curated collection of free music suitable for videos, this library allows you to use tracks without copyright issues, as long as you follow the attribution guidelines.\n\n10. **Open Music Archive**: This archive contains music that is in the public domain or has been released under creative commons licenses. You can search for genres and find suitable instrumental tracks.\n\nAlways ensure to check the specific licensing requirements and give appropriate credit where required when using music from these sources.",
